sh
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch wireguard remove' command family
# Terminal functions for removing configs and links
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Executes commands output by _wireguard_remove* functions
#   Handles removal with safety checks for active sessions and references
#
# Usage patterns:
#   vpn-switch wireguard remove <name>             → _wireguard_remove1 (removes config/link from protocol dir)
#   vpn-switch wireguard remove <category> <name>  → _wireguard_remove2 (removes link from category)
#
# Safety: Config files are checked for active sessions and symlink references before removal
